OL,3,CVeteran radio star Johnnie Walker dies
OL,4,Caged 79
OL,6,FVeteran radio DJ Johnnie Walker has
OL,7,Fdied at the age of 79, it has been
OL,8,Fannounced.
OL,10,FHis death was announced on air by his
OL,11,Ffriend and colleague, BBC Radio 2's
OL,12,FBob Harris, who took over presenting
OL,13,FSounds of the 70s in November when
OL,14,FWalker stepped down due to ill health.
OL,16,FBorn in Birmingham in March 1945,
OL,17,FWalker started out as a pirate radio
OL,18,FDJ and soon became a successful BBC
OL,19,Fpresenter with a career spanning more
OL,20,Fthan half a century.
